description: The U.S. Treasury ran a surplus last month, thanks in part to the April 15th tax deadline. But the federal government is still expected to end the year more than $1.5 trillion in the red.
title: Tax revenue jumps 22% in April. But US deficit still looms large

description: The assembly voted by a wide margin to grant new "rights and privileges" to Palestine and called on the Security Council to reconsider the Palestinians' request to become a U.N. member.
title: The U.N. General Assembly backs the Palestinians' membership bid

description: A Los Angeles Superior Court judge approved the conservatorship Thursday, noting that Brian Wilson suffers from "a major cognitive disorder." Wilson has agreed to the conservatorship.
title: Brian Wilson of The Beach Boys is being placed under a legal conservatorship

description: Olivia and Liam are the most popular baby names in the U.S. for the fifth consecutive year, according to an annual tally by the Social Security Administration.
title: 10 most popular baby names in US— Liam and Olivia dominate. Mateo rising

description: The new rule allows immigration oficials to speed up the asylum-petitioning process by assessing the person's criminal background within days, instead of months or even years.
title: Biden's new asylum rule would have 'minimal' impact on unauthorized border crossings

description: An aurora could be visible as far south as Northern California. Experts say the storm could disrupt some communications and navigation systems like GPS.
title: A huge solar storm is hurtling toward the Earth. Scientists say you should look up

description: The government has declared May 10 a day of mourning to mark the deaths from disastrous floods and pledged to help. But some say the authorities aren't doing enough. And the rains keep falling.
title: In Kenya's flooded slums, people mourn their losses and slam their leaders

description: A three-judge panel upheld the former Trump adviser's conviction for criminal contempt of Congress. The case is related to Bannon's refusal to cooperate with a House panel probe of the Jan. 6 riot.
title: Steve Bannon loses his appeal of his contempt of Congress conviction

description: Spoiler alert: It's a bug. It flies. And it bites. There's no "Ken-fusion" about the fear factor of a mosquito's bite.
title: Ryan Gosling has the correct answer to Colbert's question about the scariest animal

description: Dr. Denis Mukwege, co-winner of the Nobel peace prize in 2018, is the recipient of the $1 million Aurora humanitarian prize. In an interview with NPR, he reflects on how his campaign is
title: He fights sexual violence. He's won a Nobel and now a $1 million honor. Is he hopeful?

description: Yes, it's possible to get around without relying on GPS, say navigation experts. The first step is to let go of your fear of getting lost.
title: Terrible at directions? Tricks to improve your navigation skills

description: A former law clerk who had a bad experience on the job is now trying to share information about judges to help others from suffering the same fate.
title: Meet the lawyer who's trying to flag judges who harass their clerks

description: A pier off Gaza for aid is expected to be installed soon, but aid workers have questions. RFK Jr. says doctors found a dead worm in his brain. The WHO says he's not alone.
title: Aid workers are doubtful of a U.S.-built pier near Gaza; RFK Jr.'s dead brain worm

description: The newest iPad ad depicts instruments, books and art supplies flattened into Apple's thinnest product ever. But anyone who owns and loves art in any form knows: The practicality isn't the point.
title: Yes, Apple's new iPad ad is ugly and crushing, but art can't be flattened

description: As part of the "We, The Voters" series exploring immigration, we meet Republican Rep. Juan Ciscomani, a Mexican American representing Arizona's Sixth Congressional District.
title: What Arizona's Mexico-born Republican congressman thinks of the border situation

description: Service charges; resort fees; "surcharge" add-ons: A new state law requiring price transparency is set to take effect in July. Until now, no one knew how it would apply to restaurants.
title: California says restaurants must bake all of their add-on fees into menu prices

description: This week began with the Met Gala, which brought much-needed pageantry to the everyday lives of mortals. There was also real estate, dating apps, resignations and more.
title: Why is a teen Trump in the news? Find out in the quiz

description: Before, teams could travel on chartered flights during the postseason and for back-to-back games in the regular season. Many players said the change will make recovery easier and make them feel safer.
title: WNBA teams will travel on chartered flights for the next 2 seasons, the league says

description: Viral images of the flyer were filmed in portable toilets of a migrant camp in Mexico, and they energized members of Congress. But NPR's reporting suggests the flyer is not what it purports to be.

description: The debris from Lahaina's fire contains toxic chemicals and sits right next to a coral reef. So the community is collaborating with scientists to track water quality.
title: Maui community mobilizes to protect water quality from runoff after Lahaina fires

description: Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas sat with Morning Edition to discuss the president's approach to migrant arrivals and where he feels the strategy has worked.
title: Is Biden's border plan working? Here's how the top immigration official says it is

description: Two skiers were killed and one was rescued after they were buried in an avalanche in the mountains outside of Salt Lake City that occurred after several days of spring snowstorms, authorities said.
title: 2 skiers killed after being caught in Utah avalanche, sheriff says

description: The Senate passed a bill designed to improve safety and customer service for air travelers, a day before the law governing the Federal Aviation Administration expires.
title: Senate passes FAA reauthorization bill, sending bill to the House
